model_explanation: the focus in S1 is on Ellen and bananas, meaning Ellen only got bananas. S2 says Sam also gave Ellen grapes, which contradicts the exclusivity implied by "only" in S1.

S1 states that Mary only received apples. This implies Mary did not receive anything else, including oranges. S2 explicitly says Sam didn't give Mary oranges, which aligns with that implication, so S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 states that Tom only got bananas, emphasizing exclusivity of what Tom received. S2 says that Tom also got apples, directly contradicting the exclusivity asserted in S1.
S1 indicates Mary exclusively received apples and nothing else, which entails that Mary did not receive grapes. Therefore, S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 states Mary exclusively received oranges, meaning she didn’t receive anything else. S2 confirms she didn’t receive apples, which follows directly from the exclusivity implied by S1.

S1 states that Sam only gave Rob apples. It does not state anything about what Sam did or didn’t give to Mary. S2 talks about Mary receiving apples, which is independent of the information in S1. There is no contradiction or entailment.
S1 says that Rob was the only one to receive apples. S2 introducing Tom as also receiving apples contradicts this exclusivity.
if Rob only received oranges, it means Rob didn’t receive bananas or anything else. S2 stating that Rob didn’t get bananas is entailed by that exclusivity.
S1 says that Bill was the only one to receive grapes. S2 introducing Rob as also receiving grapes contradicts the exclusivity stated in S1.
S1 emphasizes that Rob exclusively received grapes and nothing else. S2 asserts that Rob also received bananas, which directly contradicts the exclusivity in S1.
